The paper deals with the problem of automatically building a Knowledge Graph (KG) for a specific domain, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves factorizing Open Information Extraction (OpenIE) triples extracted from a domain corpus, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves extensive experiments on multiple real-world datasets, which is a common practice in information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB).
